      <label class="med-gray h5 mb2 block">Instructor</label>
      <div class="flex underline-link mb3">
        <div class="flex-none mr3">
            <img width="80" src="https://hackdesign.imgix.net/curators/amythibodeau@2x.jpg?ixlib=rails-2.1.4&dpr=2&w=80&h=80&fit=crop&fm=jpeg&auto=format&mask=ellipse&s=671dac45f30552fa749a30865c060bb6" alt="Amythibodeau@2x.jpg?ixlib=rails 2.1" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-auto">
          <h5 class="h3 mt0 mb1 regular dark-blue">Amy Thibodeau</h5>
          <h5 class="h4 mt0 mb1 med-gray regular">
              Content Strategist, 
              <a target="_blank" href="http://facebook.com">Facebook</a>
          </h5>
          <p class="med-gray">I'm a writer and content strategist at <a href="https://www.facebook.com/amy.thibodeau" target="_blank">Facebook</a> where I focus on making <a href="https://www.facebook.com/notes/facebook-design/pages-redesign-qa-with-content-strategist-amy-thibodeau/10150623821582793" target="_blank">interfaces for businesses</a> easier to use and jargon-free. In my spare time, I dabble in photography, occasionally write about language for <a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/mind-your-language/2012/sep/14/mind-your-language-emoticons" target="_blank">The Guardian</a>, and collect ephemera on <a href="http://amythibodeau.com/" target="_blank">my blog</a>. Previously, I travelled around the world working on <a href="http://contentini.com/" target="_blank">Contentini</a>, a boutique web agency I co-founded.</p>
        </div>
      </div>


